{
  "texts": [
    "In yet another study [31], there were central entities called Attribute Authorization Centers, which were responsible for providing attribute authentication and key distribution services to users.",
    "Furthermore, researchers [32] used a semi-trusted party named Key-issuer.",
    "The key-issuer generated keys for authorized staff members upon their request to access parts of the record.",
    "Central entities are vulnerable to attacks.",
    "In another study [29], a central entity called the Regulator was included.In study [8], the encrypted patient EMRs were recorded both on the blockchain and on the cloud server."
  ]
}